				</tooltip>
				<tooltip id="BtnC_tt">
					<description>Here you can configure what action is executed for each click of the button/hotkey pressed. Left click will always open the <html:b>Sanitizer</html:b> menu and Right click will always open CustomButtons context menu.&#xA;&#xA;</description>
					<description><html:b>Notice 1:</html:b> The tabs handling options are attached to button clicks themselves, not to the actions performed when clicking. This allows certain configurations that make no sense. For example, a button click can be configured to <html:b>Clear All Data</html:b>, <html:b>Restart</html:b> your browser and <html:b>Reload all tabs</html:b>. That makes absolutely no sense. So, in situations like this, the tabs handling options will be ignored.</description>
					<description><html:b>Notice 2:</html:b> In the event that the <html:b>Options</html:b> menu item is hidden, it is <html:b>MANDATORY</html:b> that at least one button click is set to <html:b>Open Options</html:b>. As a security measure, if you hide the <html:b>Options</html:b> menu item without configuring any click to <html:b>Open Options</html:b>, <html:b>Control + Right click</html:b> will be enforced for that task.</description>
				</tooltip>
				<tooltip id="BtnCTabHandling_tt">
					<description>What to do with currently opened tabs?</description>
				</tooltip>
				<tooltip id="cad_warning_tt">
					<description>Performs the actions of <html:b>ALL</html:b> menu items <html:b>SIMULTANEOUSLY (HIDDEN MENU ITEMS INCLUDED)</html:b>.&#xA;&#xA;<html:b class="warning">THINK CAREFULLY BEFORE USING THIS OPTION</html:b>
					</description>
				</tooltip>
				<tooltip id="cad_safe_tt">
					<description>Performs the actions of <html:b>ONLY VISIBLE</html:b> menu items <html:b>SIMULTANEOUSLY</html:b>. <html:b>OV</html:b> stands for Only Visible.&#xA;&#xA; <html:b class="safe">BETTER USE THIS OPTION FOR YOUR OWN GOOD</html:b>
					</description>
				</tooltip>
				<tooltip id="BtnCTimeRange_tt">
					<description>Here can be chosen how much of the history will be cleared.</description>
					<description>When this option is set to <html:b>Default</html:b>, the executed action will take into account the preference called <html:b>Time range to clear</html:b>, which is located in the <html:b>Settings</html:b> tab of this <html:b>Preference Window</html:b>.</description>
				</tooltip>
				<tooltip id="hotkey_tt">
					<description>For this option to work, a Hotkey has to be configured in the tab called &quot;Buttons Settings&quot; of this button (accessible when editing this button).&#xA;&#xA;</description>
					<description>For example, the key combination Ctrl+Shift+Delete (used to open the Clear history native dialog), can be hijacked to perform any desired action.</description>
					<description><html:b>Note:</html:b> To delete a Hotkey, just click the Hotkey input box and press the Escape key. That will clear the currently configured Hotkey.</description>
				</tooltip>
				<tooltip id="PopupPosition_tt">
					<description>Popups are normally positioned automatically. In case the automatic position is not liked, here can be forced a custom position.</description>
					<description>See the tooltips of each position for a preview.</description>
				</tooltip>
				<tooltip id="PopupPosition_preview_tt" onpopupshowing="fromButton.Sanitizer.populatePositioningTooltip(event, this);event.stopPropagation();" onpopuphiding="event.stopPropagation();" />
				<menupopup id="sanitizer-settings" position="before_start">
					<menuitem id="defaults_prefs" label="Restore Defaults" oncommand="fromButton.Sanitizer.prefHandling.resetP(window);" />
					<menuitem id="import_prefs" label="Import Sanitizer Preferences" oncommand="fromButton.Sanitizer.prefHandling.importP(window);" />
					<menuitem id="export_prefs" label="Export Sanitizer Preferences" oncommand="fromButton.Sanitizer.prefHandling.exportP();" />
				</menupopup>
			</popupset>
		</prefwindow>
